On Nov 5, 2012, at 5:10 PM, "Shane 'Ozx' Dupree" <ozxfox@gmail.com> wrote:

> Glad to hear you pulled out a good deal in the end. That's the kind of shop
> you want to keep going back to. If it's not a VW specialist, then next time
> you might want to get an estimate (if they'll do it for free) from a shop
> that is, before you take it back to the other place. I know one top-notch
> VW shop in Cambridge, and the VW place in Union Square is pretty good, plus
> you can usually negotiate them down in price a little bit. (One time I got
> a wheel bearing replaced for almost free just because the guy didn't want
> me to have to do it myself.)
> 
> Of old Volkswagens, I'll say this: they're great fun, but they are a
> constant hassle. When they work, I think they are more fun than any other
> car. When they don't, they tend to be both expensive and difficult to fix.
> 
>  -Ozx
